An NGO has urged the Kwale county government to budget for a cerebral palsy children s facility.Kids Care Kenya director Ali Mwaziro said the county should fund, build and staff a centre to admit children with cerebral palsy so they can get an education, like others. The deaf, dumb and mentally disabled children have schools where they get an education but cerebral palsy patients have nowhere to go, he said.Mwaziro said the cerebral palsy cases children have rights to education and care like other Kenyans. We have seen our county doing a lot in putting up ECDEs, but we ask the leaders to consider this category of children, he said.Mwaziro spoke during the Yes We Can launch of a new programme targeting cerebral palsy cases.He said the project provide physical therapy for 60 children.